Feel free to add what they did in here.  Peter made a first pass 
to get the file started, but doesn´t really know who did what.


Daniel.Lemay ampersand ec.gc.ca  -- lead developer/maintainer.
generalized priorities to senders.  Second pass at file exchanger:
moved from imperative to oo style.  Second pass at the socket senders.  
many bug-fixes on all areas.  Revision control master.


Michel.Grenier ampersand ec.gc.ca --  Developer/User.
added station name extraction in bulletin headers for certain 
bulletin types.  added directory tree builder to ftp sender.
Added segmenting of messages on reception.


Louis-Phillippe.Theriault  ampersand ec.gc.ca -- Early Developer
First pass at design, all the early proofs of concept.  First receiver, 
He who chose Python over C.  First sender, and all the complex data 
transformations necesary on receipt of messages.  First pass at Bulletin Collection.  
After the first pass, and some review, implemented a second pass design 
with more OO methodologies.

Kaveh.Asfar & Travis Tiegs  ampersand ec.gc.ca -- Developer.
Team in Downsview worked on second pass at bulletin collection.

Pierre.Michaud ampersand ec.gc.ca -- Early Designer/Developer
Worked with Louis-Phillippe of the second pass design.  Developer of the first 
pass socket senders for AM, WMO, & AMIS.


Anne-Marie.Beaubien ampersand ec.gc.ca  -- Project lead
Responsible for testing, lead QA, general bulwark 
against unreliability.  head of specification team.  Most of the specs.
lead on precursor project to develop ¨Requirements for an NMMHS¨ 

  
Peter.Silva ampersand ec.gc.ca -- Project Manager.
Some requirements, first pass at the file exchange 
tracking module to allow for priorities & direct routing, and provide
an overall view of all circuits, as opposed to individual ones.



Alfred.Gagne ampersand ec.gc.ca -- He who knows the data.  
WMO messaging standards expert.  participated in specification effort, 
also testing.
  
Lambros.Stamadianos, Dave.Spiegl  ampersand ec.gc.ca 
  participated in specs for the precursor of this project.

